    </mrow>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>ii(lambda) = 657459439.291683 "unitsml(fm)"</asciimath></stem></p>
</dd>
</dl>

<p id="_1a50b124-ab2a-c5b2-008d-573f3f97508f">with a relative standard uncertainty of <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mn>1.8</mn>
    <mo>×</mo>
    <msup>
      <mn>10</mn>
      <mrow>
        <mi>−</mi>
        <mn>14</mn>
      </mrow>
    </msup>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>1.8 xx 10^(−14)</asciimath></stem> apply to the radiation of a laser stabilized to Ca atoms. The values correspond to the mean frequency of the two recoil-split components for atoms which are effectively stationary, i.e. the values are corrected for the second-order Doppler shift.</p>
</clause>

